<?php return '{"value":" <div xml:space=\\"preserve\\" class=\\"pgmonospaced pgheader\\">The Project Gutenberg EBook of The Adventures of Tom Sawyer, Complete<br \\/>by Mark Twain (Samuel Clemens)<br \\/><br \\/>This eBook is for the use of anyone anywhere at no cost and with<br \\/>almost no restrictions whatsoever.\\u00a0 You may copy it, give it away or<br \\/>re-use it under the terms of the Project Gutenberg License included<br \\/>with this eBook or online at www.gutenberg.net<br \\/><br \\/><br \\/>Title: The Adventures of Tom Sawyer, Complete<br \\/><br \\/>Author: Mark Twain (Samuel Clemens)<br \\/><br \\/>Release Date: August 20, 2006 [EBook #74]<br \\/>Last Updated: May 25, 2018<br \\/>Language: English<br \\/><br \\/><br \\/>*** START OF THIS PROJECT GUTENBERG EBOOK TOM SAWYER ***<br \\/><br \\/><br \\/><br \\/><br \\/>Produced by David Widger<br \\/><br \\/><br \\/><\\/div> <p><br \\/><\\/p> <p><br \\/><\\/p> <p><br \\/><\\/p> <hr \\/> <p><br \\/><\\/p> <div class=\\"fig c2\\"><br \\/><\\/div> <p><br \\/> <br \\/> <br \\/><\\/p> <div class=\\"fig c3\\"><img alt=\\"spine.jpg (33K)\\" src=\\"\\/751f4c3903bc00697daecc03a90f79601068f8b6.jpg\\" class=\\"c1\\" \\/><br \\/><\\/div> <p><br \\/> <br \\/> <br \\/><\\/p> <h1 id=\\"pgepubid00000\\">THE ADVENTURES OF TOM SAWYER<\\/h1> <p><br \\/> <br \\/><\\/p> <h2>BY MARK TWAIN<\\/h2> <h3 id=\\"pgepubid00001\\">(Samuel Langhorne Clemens)<\\/h3> <p><br \\/> <br \\/> <a id=\\"frontispiece\\"><\\/a><br \\/><\\/p> <div class=\\"fig c2\\"><img alt=\\"frontispiece.jpg (259K)\\" src=\\"\\/d5345f045dd0da0478f4c2b1bc3dbe07ba6f3939.jpg\\" class=\\"c1\\" \\/><br \\/><\\/div> <p><br \\/> <br \\/> <br \\/><\\/p> <div class=\\"fig c2\\"><img alt=\\"titlepage.jpg (72K)\\" src=\\"\\/77847b8bc15d08441923342e88cc64a33d257db6.jpg\\" class=\\"c1\\" \\/><br \\/><\\/div> <p><br \\/> <br \\/> <br \\/><\\/p> <div class=\\"fig c2\\"><img alt=\\"dedication.jpg (10K)\\" src=\\"\\/37b00528b482c2f353b4ac37259a4c577dd101ab.jpg\\" class=\\"c1\\" \\/><br \\/><\\/div> <p><br \\/> <br \\/> <br \\/> <br \\/><\\/p> <h2 id=\\"pgepubid00002\\">CONTENTS<\\/h2> <p><a>CHAPTER I.<\\/a><br \\/> Y-o-u-u Tom-Aunt Polly Decides Upon her Duty<br \\/> \\u2014Tom Practices Music\\u2014The Challenge\\u2014A Private Entrance<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER II.<\\/a><br \\/> Strong Temptations\\u2014Strategic Movements<br \\/> \\u2014The Innocents Beguiled<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER III.<\\/a><br \\/> Tom as a General\\u2014Triumph and Reward<br \\/> \\u2014Dismal Felicity\\u2014Commission and Omission<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER IV.<\\/a><br \\/> Mental Acrobatics\\u2014Attending Sunday\\u2014School<br \\/> \\u2014The Superintendent\\u2014\\u201cShowing off\\u201d\\u2014Tom Lionized<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER V.<\\/a><br \\/> A Useful Minister\\u2014In Church\\u2014The Climax<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER VI.<\\/a><br \\/> Self-Examination\\u2014Dentistry\\u2014The Midnight Charm<br \\/> \\u2014Witches and Devils\\u2014Cautious Approaches\\u2014Happy Hours<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER VII.<\\/a><br \\/> A Treaty Entered Into\\u2014Early Lessons\\u2014A Mistake Made<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER VIII.<\\/a><br \\/> Tom Decides on his Course\\u2014Old Scenes Re-enacted<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER IX.<\\/a><br \\/> A Solemn Situation\\u2014Grave Subjects Introduced<br \\/> \\u2014Injun Joe Explains<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER X.<\\/a><br \\/> The Solemn Oath\\u2014Terror Brings Repentance<br \\/> \\u2014Mental Punishment<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XI.<\\/a><br \\/> Muff Potter Comes Himself\\u2014Tom\\u2019s Conscience at Work<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XII.<\\/a><br \\/> Tom Shows his Generosity\\u2014Aunt Polly Weakens<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XIII.<\\/a><br \\/> The Young Pirates\\u2014Going to the Rendezvous<br \\/> \\u2014The Camp\\u2014Fire Talk<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XIV.<\\/a><br \\/> Camp-Life\\u2014A Sensation\\u2014Tom Steals Away from Camp<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XV.<\\/a><br \\/> Tom Reconnoiters\\u2014Learns the Situation\\u2014Reports at Camp<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XVI.<\\/a><br \\/> A Day\\u2019s Amusements\\u2014Tom Reveals a Secret\\u2014The Pirates<br \\/> take a Lesson \\u2014A Night Surprise\\u2014An Indian War<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XVII.<\\/a><br \\/> Memories of the Lost Heroes\\u2014The Point in Tom\\u2019s Secret<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XVIII.<\\/a><br \\/> Tom\\u2019s Feelings Investigated\\u2014Wonderful Dream<br \\/> \\u2014Becky Thatcher Overshadowed<br \\/> \\u2014Tom Becomes Jealous\\u2014Black Revenge<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XIX.<\\/a><br \\/> Tom Tells the Truth<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XX.<\\/a><br \\/> Becky in a Dilemma<br \\/> \\u2014Tom\\u2019s Nobility Asserts Itself<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXI.<\\/a><br \\/> Youthful Eloquence\\u2014Compositions by the<br \\/> Young Ladies\\u2014A Lengthy Vision<br \\/> \\u2014The Boy\\u2019s Vengeance Satisfied<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXII.<\\/a><br \\/> Tom\\u2019s Confidence Betrayed<br \\/> \\u2014Expects Signal Punishment<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXIII.<\\/a> Old Muff\\u2019s Friends\\u2014Muff Potter in Court<br \\/> \\u2014Muff Potter Saved<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXIV.<\\/a> Tom as the Village Hero\\u2014Days of Splendor<br \\/> and Nights of Horror\\u2014Pursuit of Injun Joe<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXV.<\\/a> About Kings and Diamonds\\u2014Search for the Treasure<br \\/> \\u2014Dead People and Ghosts<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXVI.<\\/a> The Haunted House\\u2014Sleepy Ghosts<br \\/> \\u2014A Box of Gold\\u2014Bitter Luck<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXVII.<\\/a> Doubts to be Settled\\u2014The Young Detectives<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXVIII.<\\/a><br \\/> An Attempt at No. Two\\u2014Huck Mounts Guard<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXIX.<\\/a><br \\/> The Pic-nic\\u2014Huck on Injun Joe\\u2019s Track<br \\/> \\u2014The \\u201cRevenge\\u201d Job\\u2014Aid for the Widow<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXX.<\\/a><br \\/> The Welchman Reports\\u2014Huck Under Fire\\u2014The Story Circulated<br \\/> \\u2014A New Sensation\\u2014Hope Giving Way to Despair<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXXI.<\\/a><br \\/> An Exploring Expedition\\u2014Trouble Commences<br \\/> \\u2014Lost in the Cave\\u2014Total Darkness\\u2014Found but not Saved<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXXII.<\\/a><br \\/> Tom tells the Story of their Escape<br \\/> \\u2014Tom\\u2019s Enemy in Safe Quarters<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXXIII.<\\/a><br \\/> The Fate of Injun Joe\\u2014Huck and Tom Compare Notes<br \\/> \\u2014An Expedition to the Cave\\u2014Protection Against Ghosts<br \\/> \\u2014\\u201cAn Awful Snug Place\\u201d\\u2014A Reception at the Widow Douglas\\u2019s<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXXIV.<\\/a><br \\/> Springing a Secret\\u2014Mr. Jones\\u2019 Surprise a Failure<br \\/> <br \\/> <a>CHAPTER XXXV.<\\/a><br \\/> A New Order of Things\\u2014Poor Huck\\u2014New Adventures Planned<br \\/> <br \\/> <br \\/> <br \\/> <br \\/> <br \\/><\\/p> <h2 id=\\"pgepubid00003\\">ILLUSTRATIONS<\\/h2> <p><a>Tom Sawyer<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Tom at Home<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Aunt Polly Beguiled<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>A Good Opportunity<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Who\\u2019s Afraid<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Late Home<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Jim<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>\'Tendin\\u2019 to Business<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Ain\\u2019t that Work?<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Cat and Toys<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Amusement<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Becky Thatcher<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Paying Off<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>After the Battle<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>\\"Showing Off\\"<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Not Amiss<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Mary<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Tom Contemplating<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Dampened Ardor<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Youth<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Boyhood<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Using the \\u201cBarlow\\"<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>The Church<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Necessities<\\/a><br \\/> <br \\/> <a>Tom as a Sunday-School He